rComments: Took this class in the summer. Easy A! I enjoyed it so much. Shes very sweet and caring. Had 2 midterms and a 3000 word essay. Got an A+ on the final! The movies, videos, documentaries were so interesting! Just pay attention, write a few notes and you have your A!
The readings can be long. The exams are very easy, they're all multiple choice except for the final exam.

She's a good prof don't get me wrong, you can manage an easy A in her class BUT SHE DOES NOT REPLY TO EMAILS EVEN IF HER LIFE DEPENDED ON IT. I HAD A MISTAKE IN MY FINAL AND SHE NEVER EVEN GOT BACK TO ME TO FIX IT AND NOW IM STUCK. so ya easy A but disrespectful when it comes to emails, never accessible outside of class so make sure u ask in class!

Prof T's Arab cinema class was *SO* *GOOD*. I truly loved it. Do keep in mind that I had the one hour version of the lectures and not three because of covid. That aside, the lectures were interesting, the movies were fascinating, and May herself is so sweet and very excited about the subject matter which always makes it so much more pleasant. 10/10

I took her class in the summer. Shes nice, but kinda strict. I had to drop her class because she wanted us to write a 3000-word essay as a final exam, without having the questions in advance to prepare. Had to drop the class. Also, her multiple choice questions were tricky, so look out for that.

She was so unnecessarily difficult for this course and was not clear on the final exam format at all. The class didn't even know when it was going to be because she posted something different than uozone and she even posted the final exam half an hour late. Very unprofessional and her lectures were useless. Too many long readings. Not a good prof.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Test heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Literally my favourite prof ever! Her lectures are a bit dry, but her passion livens it up! The class is hybrid (6 weeks in class, 6 online). No midterms, but each online week has little quizzes worth 5%. Final was a 10-12 page paper. I wrote my paper the week before and got an A+. She's an easy grader and a wonderful woman!

Her lectures feel six hours long, difficult marker and feedback is vague. She is very pretentious. Only take her class if you know you'll LOVE the subject matter. My only bad experience with a prof during my four years at UOttawa and I'll never forget how she treated me.

One of the most amazing professors at the university. She truly cares about her courses and her students. Her marking criteria is very clear and fair. Attendance is 10% and the work is really just quizzes and a final paper. No midterm. Very enjoyable class and not at all difficult. The second half of the semester is fully online.

May is literally the best. She genuinely cares for her students. Best part is that her classes are hybrid! Half online, half in class. It's essential to attend the in class cause of attendance. If you're confused, email her and she'll reply quick. Do the online quizzes and you'll do great! The final is either a video or paper. No MT.

One of the most amazing professors I have ever had in my entire life. She puts so much care and effort into her lectures. She lectures are captivating. She's a fair marker. She wants her students to do well. As long as you show up and do the quizzes and papers, you're bound to do well.
Amazing prof! Super knowledgeable and charismatic.
Amazing prof.

Shes a very passionate woman when it comes to teaching. Her class is very easy. Midterms are easy. there online and the answers are in the readings. Show up to every class and you will get an A for sure

She is one of my favourite professors I've had in my 4 years! Prof. Telmissany is very passionate and knowledgeable about the topic/course. She is extremely friendly and is available outside of class for extra help. The course is very organized and she provides lots of examples! Would definitely recommend!

She is very, very passionate about what she teaches, and she is very knowledgeable. There are weekly readings, and weekly modules, as well as quizzes. Be sure to pay attention, as the quizzes are specific. There is no final exam, just a final paper. It's a hybrid summer course, so you only need to show up 3-4 times - super easy, perfect for summer

Great prof. Her classes are very interesting. Nice style of teaching. She 's a wealth of knowledge (about  a wide range of topics). She is very driven and accomplished. Always looked forward to each class. She's laid back and doesn't stress you out about her material and assignments. To conclude, she is the most interesting women I've ever met.
did not like her teaching method.. lips so hard not to laugh and calls out students. wasn't very helpful. and exams contain specific questions. tougher then should be
Wasn't a big fan of the class or its type of midterm questions.
I had her for all the arab culture classes... she is AMAZING!! Her passion for the topic really shows, and as long as you show up/do the readings, you'll do great. :) I definitely recommend her!
She is very good and easy to understand. Easy class. She likes answering questions, even if they are a bit off topic.

May genuinely wants all of her students to succeed and will spend much more time helping you at her office than most profs would. Her passion is contagious and she is always able to wake up the class with a good joke when grammar classes drag-on. She is one of a kind - highly recommended as an Arabic language professor!
She's a really nice and fun teacher. she is a kid at heart. as long as you do your assignments you are fine! really really easy prof.. i loved her
Great Prof! She  explains arabic grammar very well. Speaks French as well. (If you already speak arabic, take her class..she won't kick you out!)
